claims:
Claims 1. A material for packing or wrapping an item or article, comprising: a laminate comprising a first layer and a second layer with an adhesive disposed therebetween, wherein the adhesive releasably bonds the first and second layers together, wherein the second layer comprises a plurality of selectively removable portions for exposing the adhesive between the first and second layers, wherein at least one of the selectively removable portions is individually and/or discretely removable from the material. 2. The material of claim 1 , wherein at least one of the selectively removable portions is removable by a user or machine for allowing the exposed adhesive to be used for securing or bonding one part of the material to another part of the material to at least partially pack or wrap the item or article. 3. The material of claim 1 or 2, wherein a number, position, size and/or dimension of the selectively removable portions for removal by a user or machine is determinable by the user or machine based on a size and/or dimension of the item or article for packing or wrapping. 4. The material of claim 1 , 2 or 3, wherein the material comprises written and/or diagrammatic instructions for helping a user or machine to ascertain which selectively removable portions to remove based on a size and/or dimension of the item or article to be packed or wrapped. 5. The material of any preceding claim, wherein the first and second layers are coextensive. 6. The material of any preceding claim, wherein the second layer comprises padding configured to provide protection for an item or article when, in use, the item or article is packed or wrapped with the material. 7. The material of any preceding claim, wherein the adhesive is configured to remain substantially bonded to the first layer such that, in use, when a selectively 

 removable portion of the second layer is removed from the material to expose the adhesive, the adhesive remains substantially bonded to the first layer. 8. The material of any preceding claim, wherein the second layer comprises at least one weakened or separable portion along a sub-track defining a boundary of at least one selectively removable portion of the second layer. 9. The material of claim 8, wherein the at least one weakened or separable portion comprises perforations. 10. The material of claim 8 or 9, wherein the second layer comprises at least one pocket of trapped gas configured to provide padding, the at least one trapped pocket of gas arranged adjacent to the at least one weakened or separable portion of the second layer. 1 1. The material of any preceding claim, wherein the first and second layers comprise co-extending portions configured to be selectively removable from the material. 12. The material of claim 1 1 , wherein the first layer and the second layer comprise at least one weakened or separable portion along a main track defining a boundary of at least one co-extending portion of the packaging material. 13. The material of claim 12, wherein the at least one weakened or separable portion of the first and second layers comprises perforations. 14. The material of claim 12 or 13, wherein the at least one weakened or separable portion of the first layer is configured to be separable using a first predetermined force or impulse acting across or between the at least one weakened or separable portion of the first layer, wherein the first predetermined force is greater than a second predetermined force or impulse for separating at least one weakened or separable portion of the second layer. 15. A process for manufacturing a material for packing or wrapping an item or article, comprising: providing a first layer and a second layer; 

 configuring the second layer to comprise a plurality of selectively removable portions; providing an adhesive between the first layer and the second layer; and bonding the first layer to the second layer, wherein at least one of the selectively removable portions is configured to be individually and/or discretely removable from the material, and wherein the selectively removable portions are configured for exposing the adhesive between the first and second layers. 16. The process of claim 15, wherein the process comprises configuring at least one of the selectively removable portions to be removable by a user or machine for allowing the exposed adhesive to be used for securing or bonding one part of the material to another part of the material to at least partially pack or wrap the item or article. 17. The process of claim 15 or 16, wherein the process comprises configuring the material such that a number, position, size and/or dimension of the selectively removable portions for removal by a user or machine is determinable by the user or machine based on a size and/or dimension of the item or article for packing or wrapping. 18. The process of claim 15, 16 or 17, wherein the process comprises providing written and/or diagrammatic instructions on the material for helping a user or machine to ascertain which selectively removable portions to remove based on a size and/or dimension of the item or article to be packed or wrapped. 19. The process of any one of claims 15 to 18, comprising adapting at least one of the first and second layers such that at least one of the first and second layers comprise at least one selectively removable portion. 20. The process of any one of claims 15 to 19, comprising weakening at least part of the second layer, or configuring at least part of the second layer to be separable, along a sub-track defining a border of the selectively removable portion of the second layer. 21. The process of claim 20, wherein weakening at least part of the second layer, or configuring at least part of the second layer to be separable, comprises perforating at least part of the second layer. 22. The process of any one of claims 15 to 21 , comprising forming pockets of trapped gas within the second layer to provide padding, wherein at least one pocket of trapped gas is formed adjacent to a border defined by at least one of the selectively removable portions of the second layer. 23. The process of any one of claims 15 to 22, comprising weakening at least part of the first layer and the second layer, or configuring at least part of the first layer and the second layer to be separable, along a main track defining a border of at least one selectively removable portion of the material, the removable portion of the material comprising a co-extending portion of the first and second layers. 24. The process of claim 23, wherein weakening at least part of the first layer and the second layer, or configuring at least part of the first layer and the second layer to be separable, comprises perforating at least part of the first layer and the second layer. 25. The process of claim 23 or 24, wherein the process comprises configuring the at least one weakened or separable portion of the first layer to be separable using a first predetermined force or impulse acting across or between the at least one weakened or separable portion of the first layer, wherein the first predetermined force is greater than a second predetermined force or impulse for separating at least one weakened or separable portion of the second layer.
